external-css: Keeping all the css files under a single file


inline css > internal > external css

Box Model: A box model is a Box that is wrapped around every html elements
A box model consist of :
Paddding
Margin
border

Margin:
A margin is basically a imaginary space around an HTML elements
top,right,bottom,left..
px:
syntax:
margin-top
margin-right
margin-bottom
margin-left

There is a short hand notation in which 
margin:top right botttom left

Border: A border is a Thick Visible line

Padding: It is a imaginary space around a content

Note: If you wanted to convert the block level element to the inline elemenmts
then you can use the inline properties

Table:to display the data in  terms of rows and columns


Note: Tag selectors:
tag selectors are applied to the specifics tags
ex: div, span, th, td, table..

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="index.css">
</head>
<body>
<table>
    <thead>
    <tr>
        <th>First name</th>
        <th>Middle Name</th>
        <th>Last name</th>
    </tr>
    </thead>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
        <td>John</td>
        <td>Doe </td>
        <td>Miller</td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
</table>
</body>
</html>

.main{
    background-color: yellow;
    margin-top: 2px;
    margin-left: 2px;
    border:1px double black;
    padding:2px;
    display:inline
}

table,th,td{
    border: 1px solid black;
    border-collapse: collapse;
}


Applying flexibility to the website

Flex Box
Flexibele box
Its Applied over single direction(1 - D)

How - to use  the flex-box:
syntax : <display:flex></display:flex>